The pilot reported that he was landing the float equipped airplane on a lake. The winds were 
light and the lake had about 3 inch ripples on the water. He reported that the touchdown 
appeared normal, but a few seconds later the right wing went up and the left wing dipped in the 
water. The left wing was bent upward and sustained substantial damage. A witness reported 
that he observed the airplane flying slow over the water in a left bank when the airplane 
ﬁdropped into the lakeﬂ with the left wing hitting the water. The pilot reported there was no 
mechanical malfunction of the airplane.
The pilot's improper flare and touchdown during the water landing.
